  "chapter": {
    "number": 54,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Future Blessings for Zion"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Shout for joy, O barren woman,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who bears no children;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "break forth in song and cry aloud,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you who have never travailed;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "because more are the children of the desolate woman",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "than of her who has a husband,”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2708
          },
          "says the LORD."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Enlarge the site of your tent,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "stretch out the curtains of your dwellings,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "do not hold back.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Lengthen your ropes",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and drive your stakes in deep.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2709
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For you will spread out to the right and left;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "your descendants will dispossess the nations",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and inhabit the desolate cities.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do not be afraid, for you will not be put to shame;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "do not be intimidated, for you will not be humiliated.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For you will forget the shame of your youth",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and will remember no more the reproach of your widowhood.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For your husband is your Maker—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the LORD of Hosts is His name—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the Holy One of Israel is your Redeemer;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He is called the God of all the earth.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For the LORD has called you back,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like a wife deserted and wounded in spirit,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "like the rejected wife of one’s youth,”",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "says your God.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“For a brief moment I forsook you,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but with great compassion I will bring you back.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In a surge of anger",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I hid My face from you for a moment,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "but with everlasting kindness I will have compassion on you,”",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "says the LORD your Redeemer.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“For to Me this is like the days of Noah,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2710
          },
          {
            "text": "when I swore that the waters of Noah",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "would never again cover the earth.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "So I have sworn that I will not be angry with you",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or rebuke you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Though the mountains may be removed",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the hills may be shaken,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "My loving devotion will not depart from you,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and My covenant of peace will not be broken,”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "says the LORD, who has compassion on you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“O afflicted city, lashed by storms,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "without solace,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "surely I will set your stones in antimony",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and lay your foundations with sapphires.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2711
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will make your pinnacles of rubies,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "your gates of sparkling jewels,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and all your walls of precious stones.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then all your sons will be taught by the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2712
          },
          {
            "text": "and great will be their prosperity.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In righteousness you will be established,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "far from oppression,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for you will have no fear.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Terror will be far removed,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for it will not come near you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If anyone attacks you, it is not from Me;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "whoever assails you will fall before you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Behold, I have created the craftsman",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who fans the coals into flame",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and forges a weapon fit for its task;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and I have created the destroyer",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to wreak havoc.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "No weapon formed against you shall prosper,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and you will refute every tongue that accuses you.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "This is the heritage of the servants of the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and their vindication is from Me,”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "declares the LORD."
        ]
      }
    ],
